    <Attribute>
      <AttributeName>Gendarme.Framework.Solution("For known values it is faster to use typeof(x), C# syntax, to obtain the same result without the reflection penality.")</AttributeName>
    </Attribute>
    <Attribute>
      <AttributeName>Gendarme.Framework.Problem("This method calls Type.GetType(string) on a constant string. This call requires reflection in order return an instance of the type.")</AttributeName>
    </Attribute>
  </Attributes>
  <Docs>
    <summary>
            This rule warns when a method use <c>Type.GetType(string)</c> with a constant string.
            Such calls requires reflection in order to return a <c>Type</c> instance and, for
            known types, can be replaced with a much faster <c>typeof(x)</c>.
            </summary>
    <remarks>This rule is available since Gendarme 2.0</remarks>
    <example>
            Bad example:
            <code>
            booleanType = Type.GetType ("System.Boolean");
            </code></example>
    <example>
            Good example:
            <code>
            booleanType = typeof (bool);
            </code></example>
    <example>
            Bad example:
            <code>
            booleanType = Type.GetType ("System.Boolean");
            </code></example>
    <example>
            Good example:
            <code>
            booleanType = typeof (bool);
            </code></example>
  </Docs>
